    "body": "My comment here is basically the same one as [on cargo](https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/pull/746) which is that it's unfortunate that this quotes _all_ arguments when it only really needs to quote a select number of arguments.\n\nI'm also a little wary to favor bash syntax here as there's not really a guarantee that anyone's using bash and it may favor unix too much. We're developing some new conventions for the `Show` trait to precisely explain its purpose, but the gist of it is that `Show` is intended for debugging and I don't think it necessarily needs to be a 100% accurate representation of the underlying primitive.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
