    "body": "As mentioned previously, this is posix shell syntax, not bash syntax.\n\nEven ignoring that: the choice of syntax is irrelevnet. The goal was to make the output unambiguous so that I could debug the cause of a command failure (within cargo, as it happens) due to the contents of environment variables being less-than-ideal.\n\nI'd be happy to accept any output that I can look at and definitively know what the arguments & command are. This is one way to accomplish that. It's also probably the most recognizable way to do so, given the context of executing commands. IIRC, windows doesn't even have a standard way of parsing arguments to commands, it hands programs the whole string.\n\nAnd on removing \"unneeded\" quotes:\n- it isn't necessary for making the command unambiguous for debugging\n- it has the potential to make people wonder whether or not things are actually quoted.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
